Step to connect to a local instance of MongoDB for CRUD operations.

1. Create a data directory in the folder app. (mkdir data)
2. Set the path lo local directory: mongod --dbpath /var/www/html/dev/node_express_api
3. Open mongo: mongo and enter
4. Inside of mongo type: mongod --dbpath /var/www/html/dev/node_express_api<enter>
5. we'll see a lot of initandlisten
6. In another CLI type mongo<enter>
7. Then MongoDB say: connecting to: test.
8. Thenk type: use bear. We'll see "switched to db bear"
9. Type in server.js the connection to our local MongoDB: mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost/bear');
10. In this point we can run in CLI our server.js

